ow who to approach to craft items for us for only the cost of the materials needed to produce the item.<br><br>I should like to nominate myself as the Tinker Master of the guild, naturally, and I am well aware of Rivenshade's knack for bartending.  I am sure there are others that have taken skills far, but we are unaware of their hard work.<br><br>In closing, this is not meant to discourage those that are not Trade Masters from improving skills, for these skills are a fun part of the game.  Becoming a master is difficult, requires pps and a lot of clicks of the mouse and trips around Norrath.  But having masters will allow everyone to have a resource regarding difficult questions and allow those that need items to have them instantly at a guild price!<br><br>Just the thoughts of a little Gnome in a big big world. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#66CCFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub29.ezboard.com/uleomarth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Leomarth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Officer</span><br>  Posts: 347<br> <font color=#000099>(3/20/02 7:48:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub29.ezboard.com/fpaxfamillafrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=778.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Gnomish wheels turning.. guild suggestion:</span><hr size=1> Excellent ideal Abbrah. I think I&quot;m going to pawn the guild page off on someone soon though.    hehehe. Tomorrow I'm going to gather together all the nominations we had for officers, and put them to the officers for a vote.<br><br>Yours, Suntoucher. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#339999><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub29.ezboard.com/ufieryfistjones.showPublicProfile?language=EN>FieryFistJones</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User<